# Evaluation Criteria

{% if project_type == "frontend_only" %}
1. **Does it do what it is supposed to do?** — Every feature in the Features Request is covered in the Frontend Spec. No feature is missing implementation details.
2. **Does it work well?** — The spec is internally consistent. BaaS schema matches the UI data requirements.
3. **Is it reasonably well designed?** — Component decomposition is clean. State management is appropriate.
4. **Is it safe?** — Authentication and authorization are properly specified. BaaS security rules are defined. Sensitive data is not exposed client-side.
5. **No obvious scaling issues?** — Data access patterns are efficient. Pagination is specified where needed.
{% elif project_type == "backend_only" %}
1. **Does it do what it is supposed to do?** — Every feature in the Features Request is covered across the two specs. No feature is missing implementation details.
2. **Does it work well?** — The two specs are internally consistent. Backend services implement all API Contract endpoints.
3. **Is it reasonably well designed?** — No duplication across documents. API Contract is the single source of truth.
4. **Is it safe?** — Authentication and authorization are properly specified. No endpoints are missing auth requirements. Input validation is addressed.
5. **No obvious scaling issues?** — Data models support expected load. No N+1 query patterns. Pagination is specified where needed.
{% else %}
1. **Does it do what it is supposed to do?** — Every feature in the Features Request is covered across the three specs. No feature is missing implementation details.
2. **Does it work well?** — The three specs are internally consistent. Frontend references match API Contract endpoints. Backend services implement all API Contract endpoints.
3. **Is it reasonably well designed?** — No duplication across documents. API Contract is the single source of truth. Component decomposition is clean.
4. **Is it safe?** — Authentication and authorization are properly specified. No endpoints are missing auth requirements. Input validation is addressed.
5. **No obvious scaling issues?** — Data models support expected load. No N+1 query patterns. Pagination is specified where needed.
{% endif %}
